  "texts": [
    "It follows that for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′ and y ′′′ ⊑ y ′′, y ′′′ ̸ ⊑ x, so y ′′ ̸ ⊑ s x and hencey ′′ ̸ ∈ {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x}.",
    "Thus, {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x} satisfies refinability.Finally, we observe that ⊑ s behaves like ⊑ with respect to the forcing relation in possibility models.Fact 4.4 (Forcing and ⊑ s).",
    "For any possibility model M = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, π⟩, x, y ∈ S, and φ ∈ L(Φ, I):1.",
    "⊑ s -Persistence: if M, x ⊩ φ and y ⊑ s x, then M, y ⊩ φ; 2.",
    "⊑ s -Refinability: if M, x ⊮ φ, then ∃x ′ ⊑ s x: M, x ′ ⊩ ¬φ; 3."
